manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Republic of Gamers (ROG), part of the ASUS family, is dedicated to creating innovative hardcore gaming hardware for gamers. ROG is committed to providing the absolute best performance and quality from its complete line of products. ROG is for those keen on the finest gaming hardware and software as it enables the ultimate computing experience for gamers and enthusiasts worldwide. It incorporates a stylish gamer-focused design, merging the excitement of gaming with a unique premium style. ROG Hyperion GR701 ROG Hyperion GR701 E-ATX computer case, 420 mm dual radiator support, four 140 mm fans, metal GPU holder, component storage, ARGB fan hub, 60W fast charging. Extra Cooling: Dual 420mm radiator support, four 140 mm fans and a built-in fan hub offer massive airflow possibilities Extra Space: The beefiest graphics cards get plenty of room; cable management gets an expansive chamber that is 34 mm deep, with a 46 mm wide routing channel Extra Convenience: Hinged tool-free side panels, a built-in storage drawer and an integrated graphics card holder come together to amp up the building experience Extra Power: Dual USB Type-C ports, 60-watt fast charging, aluminum-reinforced frame and handles deliver power and premium ruggedness Extra Stylish: The fan hub and lighting panel all support Aura Sync, and the chassis is decked out with anodized metal and hairline finishes

STRUCTURE AND STYLE A front side air intake can provide ample ventilation to get just the right balance of temperatures for your system and graphics cards. This integrates tightly into a bold new look with features like the distinctive diamond-shaped badge on the front, stamped with the famous ROG logo and surrounded by diagonal slashes. BUILT FOR HIGH AIRFLOW The Republic of Gamers is populated by builders who demand the best, and the Hyperion GR701 delivers top-tier cooling potential with support for 420 mm radiators on the top and in the front of the chassis, while four 140 mm PWM fans come pre-connected to an Aura Sync ARGB fan hub. Support For 2 x 420 mm RadiatorsPre-installed 4 x 140 mm PWM Fans AMPLE CABLE MANAGEMENT AND ROUTING Underneath the motherboard tray area, builders will find a chamber 34 mm deep for their cable management needs, and a cable routing channel that’s 46 mm wide and secured by several ROG-branded Velcro straps to keep things looking tidy for the transparent side panel. This chassis also offers a translucent cable cover that can obscure unsightly wiring while letting your RGB style shine through. 1. WIDTH: 46 mm for cable routing 2. DEPTH: 34 mm for cable management

DUAL TYPE-C FAST CHARGING The front of any ROG chassis has to offer a host of connectors, and the ROG Hyperion adds to the tradition with two USB Type-C connectors that can offer up to 20 Gbps of data transfer and up to 60 watts of fast charging with a compatible motherboard. DIE-CAST ALUMINUM ALLOY FRAME The ROG Hyperion frame is constructed of rugged aluminum alloys forged into a distinctive X that extends from the center of the chassis all the way out to its perimeter. Its rigid structure doubles up as carry handles capable of bearing up to 80 kg of hardware. A ROG-THEMED LIGHTING PANEL This chassis features an internal ARGB lighting panel that communicates the ROG identity to anyone who gazes within, and it can be displayed on the outside if builders want to make room in that spot for fans or SSDs.

TOOL-FREE HINGED SIDE PANELS To maximize the ease of accessing the interior any time you want, this chassis features a hinged side panel made of tinted glass that simply swings open without requiring any tools, at which point the panel can be lifted up and out of the way if desired. HIDDEN DRAWER To make system maintenance easier, this chassis features a small integrated storage compartment for things like PCIe slot brackets, screws and cable fasteners, so your frequently used widgets are always within easy reach. BUILT-IN GRAPHICS CARD HOLDER The ROG Hyperion GR701 features a highly refined integrated graphics card holder, whose lightweight anodized aluminum components can be used vertically or horizontally to keep long graphics cards from sagging, and it offers additional compatibility with the ROG Herculx card holder.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 6, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Very sturdy, plenty of room, great airflow, and it has to be the sexiest case I have ever seen.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 12, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I got this case because of the new generation of graphics cards being so large. I have a RTX 4090 that measures 14 inches and this case makes it look tiny. Everything about this case is over the top and it is the largest case I've ever seen. It's very well built and the airflow so far seems really great. The front USB-C ports support 60W fast charging so this is the first time I've ever actually used my computer to charge my phone while I'm at my desk. Comes with 4 140mm fans and a fan/rgb hub that came in really clutch with my build. The screw driver and little drawer is actually really useful and I think it's a nice addition. This will probably be the last computer case I will ever have to buy!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Top Notch ROG PC Case
reviews.reviewText: This PC case is stylish, yet one of the most expensive gaming PC case available on the market. This case is very big, very heavy, with lots of internal space that can fit a large GPU, RTX 4090 for my case. The magnetic side panels are excellent for quick open and close when needed. Both side panels are not completely sealed, leaving space for more air flow inside to cool the internal parts. Compared to my older PC case ROG GX601, my CPU get about 8 degrees Celsius cooler.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars It’s a large tower, but worth it for RTX 4090
reviews.reviewText: If you have issues with space, I would recommend looking for mid-tower. This one is huge, but provides for excellent airflow. Playing Cyberpunk at the max settings/4K, my RTX 4090 did not exceed 72 C.Considering the price, they could have included ARGB fans, but unfortunately they did not. Had to spend another $40 just to replace them.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars This is the best case I have gotten in the past sixteen years hands down.
reviews.reviewText: It is not very often I run into a case I really like, I have owned over 100 cases the past twenty years. Only have ran into one that was pure quality out of the box and it was the last case designed by the once owner/founder of Voodoo PC sixteen years ago until now. The Hyperion is amazing out of the box, it is pre cable managed almost like someone from one of the top pc builder companies did it for you, it is easy to work with, the cooling of the exoskeletal aluminum frame. that has air drawn over it working as a passive air cooler before it has a chance to make it into the case does an amazing job. It has anything you could need out of the box, There is almost nothing you need to buy unless you want to vertically mount your gpu then you just need the pcie cable for the card, it comes with the plate for the back of the case to vertically mount plus a vertical mount support built in. The included fans are amazing with the case's passive cooling. This is by far the nicest case released that I have had the pleasure of working with in sixteen years.This review is for the 90 day warranty extension program.
